Tomcat installation steps for ubuntu server

1) Sudo apt update -y 
2) install default version of java --  sudo apt install -y openjdk-17-jdk
3) Check the version - - java --version
4) download the tomcat tar file --wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-10/v10.1.48/bin/apache-tomcat-10.1.48.tar.gz
5) Extract the downloaded archive sudo tar xzvf apache-tomcat-10.1.48.tar.gz
6) Create installation directory -- sudo mkdir -p /opt/tomcat/
7) Move extracted files to /opt/tomcat sudo mv apache-tomcat-10.1.48/* /opt/tomcat/
8) Change ownership and permissions sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /opt/tomcat/
     sudo chmod -R 755 /opt/tomcat/
9) Create a Systemd Service for Tomcat
   -- Run this complete command in your terminal
sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/tomcat.service >/dev/null <<'EOF'
[Unit]
Description=Tomcat
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=forking
User=root
Group=root
Environment="JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk-amd64/"
Environment="JAVA_OPTS=-Djava.security.egd=file:///dev/urandom"
Environment="CATALINA_BASE=/opt/tomcat"
Environment="CATALINA_HOME=/opt/tomcat"
Environment="CATALINA_PID=/opt/tomcat/temp/tomcat.pid"
Environment="CATALINA_OPTS=-Xms512M -Xmx1024M -server -XX:+UseParallelGC"
ExecStart=/opt/tomcat/bin/startup.sh
ExecStop=/opt/tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF
   
   
After running above commands check the content of the file by running -- cat /etc/systemd/system/tomcat.service

Note: The JAVA_HOME path in your script points to Java 11. If your default-jdk installed Java 17 (common on Ubuntu 22.04+), verify with:
readlink -f /usr/bin/java | sed "s:bin/java::"

Run this command and cross check the which java version is mentioned 
readlink -f /usr/bin/java | sed "s:bin/java::"



10) Configure Tomcat Users (Manager/Admin GUI)
    sudo vi /opt/tomcat/conf/tomcat-users.xml
    Add below mentioned content in tomcat-users.xml file 
	
<role rolename="manager-gui" />
<user username="manager" password="StrongPassword" roles="manager-gui,manager-script" />

<role rolename="admin-gui" />
<user username="admin" password="StrongPassword" roles="manager-gui,admin-gui" />

11) Enable Remote Access to Manager/Host-Manager 
    
sudo vi /opt/tomcat/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml
 
Comment out this lines 
 <!-- <Valve className="org.apache.catalina.valves.RemoteAddrValve"
     allow="127\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+|::1|0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1" /> -->
 
Similarly for Host-Manager:
sudo vi /opt/tomcat/webapps/host-manager/META-INF/context.xml

<!-- <Valve className="org.apache.catalina.valves.RemoteAddrValve"
     allow="127\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+|::1|0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1" /> -->



12) sudo systemctl daemon-reload
    sudo systemctl restart tomcat
	sudo systemctl status tomcat
